==English==
===Adjective===
'''prostrate'''
# Lying flat; facedown. 

===Transitive verb===
{{en-verb|prostrat|ing}}
# To lay flat or facedown, [[prone]]; flatten (oft. reflexive).
# To be rendered bedridden by a medical condition.
#:''He was '''prostrated''' by leukemia.''
# To be emotionally devestated.
#:''I told him you was '''prostrate''' with grief.'' — Mammy to Scarlett, ''Gone With the Wind''. 

====Usage note====
Prostrate and [[prostate]] are often confused, in spelling if not in meaning.

